description.narrative:
Economic Policy Research Center (EPRC) has applied to Embassy for funding of 21 000 000 SEK to carry out the project  "Increasing Competitiveness of SMEs in Georgia", in partnership with Enterprise Georgia, the state agency responsible for SME development. The duration of the project is 2018-2021. 

The intervention aims to increase domestic and international competitiveness of small and medium sized enterprises (SMEs) in Georgia. The objectives of this intervention are the following: 

1) Identification of new sectors, products and services of SMEs with high growth and expansion potential, through market and sectoral research and analysis;
2) Promoting DCFTA opportunities among SMEs to advance their domestic and international market expansion strategies, increasing skills, domestic and international competitiveness of SMEs through providing direct mentoring, educational and technical assistance, as well as bringing them in compliance with the EU’s Association Agreement and Deep and Comprehensive Free Trade Agreement (AA/DCFTA) requirements;
3) Increasing capacity of the entrepreneurship promotion agency, Enterprise Georgia, through capacity building, increased access to international markets and technical assistance of its beneficiaries.

Market research will identify sectors showing high growth and export potential on the EU market. Sector analysis will define EU standards, certifications, licences and other requirements for entering the EU market and based on this, EPRC will develop sector specific curricula and recommendations for internationalisation and export of SMEs. The intervention will provide technical assistance in the form of small grants to promising SMEs aiming to increase their competitiveness and compliance to enter into the EU market. Mentoring, advising, study tours and training will also be provided to SMEs. Selection of SMEs will be done on a competitive basis according to agreed criteria and women-led, gender focused and environmentally responsible strategies will be given special emphasis. Capacity development of Enterprise Georgia will be conducted through trainings relating to AA/DCFTA, management training and knowledge exchange through media tours from Georgia to Sweden, participation in market fairs, B2B events and study tour to a corresponding export promotion agency in a European country. Development of content and information on Enterprise Georgia's online platform "Trade with Georgia" aims to further promote international partnerships and progress Georgia's trade with international markets.
